egging Help</span><hr size=1> I am a lvl 43 Druid who recently got a bottle of Acid and The Blood wolf Harness. <br>
<br>
I have a friend a 45 mage, and he wants to help me get these leggings. There also might be a 40 enchanter coming.<br>
Is there any way we would be able to kill fergul, and what is this I hear about the broodmother being charmed or something. And about how many HP Fergul has and any special resistances would also be very helpfull. <br>
<br>
-Thank You<br>
<br>
-The Thunderspirit- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uflaim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flaim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 7:13:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> Just the 3 of you?  Naw. I don't think so.  I would not even attempt it till you get your new spells at 44, either.<br>
<br>
When you do, get 2 tanks and another healer, should be doable.<br>
<br>
You need damage, DoTs, and healing. And of course Ensnare and Root, once you get him away from the fort.<br>
<br>
He has a lot of hit points, seemed like upwards of 8K, maybe more.<br>
<br>
He was insanely non-resistant to my spells at 45, and he's 50.  Most stuck.<br>
<br>
From my impression, and just for comparison, he's like 3 Wurms in a row, if you know what I mean?  If you can do that, then you can do Fergul, I think. <p><font face=Arial size=1><b> <a href="mailto:fyyrlupinestorm@hotmail.com"><font color="#990000">Fyyr 
LupineStorm</font></a><font color="#990000"><br>
Chaotic Neutral Wanderer<br>
Master 'Small Pissed Off Deity' Potter<br>
GDI<br>
Bristlebane </font></b></font> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuteaoregalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ButeaoRegalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/01 1:27:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;He was insanely non-resistant to my spells at 45, and he's 50. Most stuck.<br>
<br>
Are you sure? I don't recall at what level I did the quest (48-49 I think) but he was blue to me.<br>
<br>
Buteao<br>
Level 52 Druid on Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucuchulainekynthelig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuchulaine Kynthelig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/01 2:34:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> I don't really know waht level he is...less than 51, for sure, because he was blue at 51. <br>
<br>
Anyway, you might have trouble with that low of a group. Maybe if you got a 50+ player that can fear, and a couple of good damage dealers, but just the three of you? Probably not. He has a TON of hitpoints, and will resist a lot of your spells. <p><a href="mailto:Cuchulaine@luclin.com">Cuchulaine Kynthelig</a> <BR>
Tunare's Wanderer for 54 Seasons<BR>
<BR>
Luclin
<BR><BR>
"Have you hugged your druid today?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalowenthunderspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talowen Thunderspirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/01 3:08:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> on track Fergul cons blue at 43, yet i don't know if he respawns stronger. The three of us have been able to handle alot, like 3 frost giants,  1 berserker, and 4 dire wolfves. ( was very fun, yet took time). But thanks to the advice i see here, i will at least wait till 44 or 45 so I can use ES vambraces, and I'll try to find a high lvl necro or someone to help us.<br>
<br>
-The Thunderspirit- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwalkerbohh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walker Bohh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/21/01 7:22:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> List your server Tal.  Yes he does repop at a higher lvl. I`m not sure if any of your spells would stick. Please- Please! call out to the zone that you are doing the quest tho   and make sure someone is at the giant fortress to talk to folks who might be coming in to kill giants. I saw a lvl 60 monk have to recamp the quest because he didnt let anyone know and his fergul was aggroed by someone and the broodmother killed him(fergul) b4 he could run away.<br>
This could really ruin a weekend.<br>
If you are on Prexus give me a yell- I`ve done this quest about 6 times now - bracer and legs for me and a couple of guildmates. Camping the broodmother is the worst part though. Good luck.<br>
<br>
Walker Boh<br>
56 Preserver<br>
Proud GuildLeader of the RagingBoars <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalowenthunderspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talowen Thunderspirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/22/01 9:32:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> I'm on the Rathe server. I have about 5k in the bank, and maybe when i hit 45 and if I can get some ES vambraces me and my friends could take him. Or i'll see if anyone in the zone or anyone in my friends guild could help. If anyone that reads this plays on the Rathe and would like to help send me a tell. I got the control harness, just need the brood mama and the killing force.<br>
<br>
-The Thunderspirit- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utulen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tulen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/22/01 11:21:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> I soloed Fergul yesterday as a 50 druid.  He does have a ton of hp,  but didn't resist me that much.  I just pulled him to the area between the fort and EW zone and just rooted/dotted him.  No other giants got close to join in here.  Just took a while by myself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubraidfreak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>braidfreak</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/22/01 12:52:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1> the biggest annoyance of this quest is getting adds.  make sure you pull him waaay up on the ledge to the left of the giant fort.  there's so much trash (scouts and wolves) around that it can be a real pain when you're trying to kill fergul.  there's another long post about the kromriff leggings that i wrote out a big list of to do's and not to do's.  might wanna search through the older pages.<br>
<br>
<br>
clairan <p>check out simplekill...a band that's about to explode and squash queer bands like korn
http://www.simplekill.net</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaelwr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelwr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/22/01 4:56:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Legging Help</span><hr size=1>  I am a 54th Druid and the normal Fergul is green to me. The one that popped during the quest however was blue. I soloed him fairly easily but he did break root 2 or 3 times. He seems comperable to the Frost Giant Elites that roam the area perhaps with a few more HP's. So if your group could easily take the Elites then Fergul shouldn't be a big problem. <br>
<br>
 I ran him around to the rear of the fort and took him up on the zone line there where I had plenty of room for him to run when he broke root. You just have to be careful as stated above to watch for adds especially when moving to the clear area. The Broodmother actually caused me more problems because she about half way into the fight attached herself sort of like a pet to Fergul. She did not however attack me if I stayed out of her range but any tanks attepting a close fight under those conditions could be in a lot of trouble quickly. I did not attack or root her and she despawned when Fergul died.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4383.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4381.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.emailToFriend?topicID=4367.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.threadControl?topicID=4367.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4367.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4367.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table borde